Common Issues & Solutions

URL Accessibility Issues

If a scraper's URL is not accessible, check if:

  • The website is still active
  • The URL has changed
  • The site blocks automated requests (consider adding headers)
Scraper Errors

Common causes of scraper failures:

  • HTML structure changes on the target website
  • Missing error handling for null/undefined values
  • Selectors no longer match the website structure
  • Timeout issues for slow-loading sites
Empty Results

If a scraper runs but returns no events:

  • The site might genuinely have no events
  • The scraper might be looking at the wrong page section
  • The date parsing might be failing
  • The scraper might need updated selectors

\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            MORE ABOUT THE MOSS\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          In a musical landscape with fewer boundaries than ever before, THE MOSS’s exuberant brand of alternative rock spans genres, eras, and even oceans.The Utah-via-Hawaii group was born on the shores of Oahu in 2015, as teenage buddies Tyke James (vocals/guitar) and Addison Sharp (guitar) picked up a gig serenading diners at local taco trucks in between surf sessions. Naturally, their songs took shape in the spirit of the island, imbued with the joyfulness and breeziness of reggae culture yet cut with the introspection and communal spirit of mainland indie acts like Pinegrove and Cage the Elephant.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n\n    \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            MORE ABOUT OLIVER HAZARD\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          While some musiciansare scheming to go viral, the Waterville, OH indie-folk band Oliver Hazard has been killing it the old-fashioned way: squeezing into a van, traversing a tangle of Interstates, and winning over fans one city at a time. They created a Living Room Tour, where one fan would host the band and invite over some friends. They played 60 shows across the U.S. in 2019 alone. Such is the ethic that’s made Oliver Hazard a case study in smarts, hustle, and unrelenting charm.Since then, Oliver Hazard — Mike Belazis (frontman), Devin East (guitarist) and Nate Miner (keyboardist) — have released a pair of albums (34 N. River, Oliver Hazard) and two EPs (The Flood, Northern Lights). The trio has gone on to headline tours, created their own festival Oliver Hazard Day, played Bonnaroo and Mountain Jam, and amassed nearly 850K Spotify monthly listeners. On December 6, the band will release its latest EP, Raindrop River (Nettwerk), a collection of warmly harmonic sing-alongs that celebrates an earnest, uncomplicated band at its peak.“Our music is a lot more heartfelt, because we’re actually playing together in a room. It’s pretty old school, but so are we,” Mike says. “Oliver Hazard wasn’t an overnight success. It’s not like we got two million followers on TikTok and all of a sudden the venues were full. We really had to be intentional about our shows. And we didn’t want to abandon that sense of place and community that helped us get to where we are.” instagram | spotify\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            MORE ABOUT Harbour\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Since their formation in 2014, HARBOUR has gone from packing rooms in their native Cincinnati, to selling out venues across the United States. Members Ryan Green (vocals/guitar), Jarett Lewis (guitar), Ryan Sulken (drums), Walker Atkinson (bass), and Devon Turner (guitar) have curated an indie pop/rock sound that has garnered millions of listeners worldwide across all music platforms.Their latest album - “To Chase My Dreams, Or To Just Lie Down?” was released in February, 2023. PNE Fairgrounds at 2901 E. Hastings in Vancouver, BC.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            REMIND ME THE BASIC DETAILS (DATE, TIME, ETC.)\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          SATURDAY JULY 12, 202512PM-4PM (Afternoon Tasting)5PM - 9PM (Evening Tasting)THE CONCERTSThe MossOliver HazardHarbourTHE PRODUCTSCraft BeerCidersBC Natural WinesWings + Other Foods\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW MUCH ARE TICKETS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Tickets start at their lowest price and as they sell and as the event gets closer, ticket prices increase.There are two categories of tickets: GA and GA+GA tickets start at $30 and will eventually end up at their regular price of $49, before selling out.GA+ tickets start at $55 and will eventually end up at their regular price of $74, before selling out. There are limited amount of GA+ tickets.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN GA AND GA+TICKETS AND WHAT IS INCLUDED IN EACH?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          GA TICKETAdmission During the Tasting its For (Aft vs. Eve)Souvenir Tasting CupThe ConcertsGA+ TICKETAll GA perks+*$30 Worth of Tokens*Private GA+ Entrance Private GA+ Bathrooms\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            IS THE EVENT RAIN OR SHINE?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yep!  We will be soaking up the rays of sun or frolicking within the drops of rain.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW DO TOKENS WORKS? HOW MUCH ARE SAMPLES?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Each product is purchased at the event using the festival token. Tokens can be pre-purchased or purchased onsite.Most, if not all beverage samples at VCBW are about $2 (+tax) worth of tokens .Food is available for purchase on site using credit/debit cards.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW DO I GET ACCESS TO THE PRE-SALE WINDOWS, DISCOUNTED TICKETS AND VIP EVENTS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Make sure you are on the Feaster list.  This is where any and all of the above will be released. Sign up for the list on the VCBW website.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            DO YOU SELL DESIGNATED DRIVER TICKETS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          We do not have a different ticket available for DDs. We welcome designated drivers and have thus the ticket is now a-la-carte in that you are just purchasing admission and if you want to sample alcohol, you’d purchase tokens to do so. Purchasing a GA ticket also gives the DD access to many food items, the concerts, non-alc beverage samples and entertainment. DO NOT DRINK AND DRIVE!\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHEN CAN I BUY TICKETS TO VCBW?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          All tickets for this event are purchased through ticketleader.ca. Pre-sale begins after March!\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            DO I NEED TO PRINT MY TICKET?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          No. All tickets are 100% mobile!\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE TICKETS REFUNDABLE?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          VCBW tickets are non-refundable. Tickets are transferable and thus can be given away to friends or sold on 3rd party sites. We do not hold any responsibility for tickets that are bought, sold, given away or received privately as there is no way to trace them to the new buyer. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHAT ABOUT IF IT IS POSTPONED?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          If the event is postponed for any reason, tickets will not be refunded.  All tickets will be valid for the next VCBW.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            IS THERE A TICKET LIMIT?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          No, there is not.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW ARE TICKETS DELIVERED?  \n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Tickets are all mobile tickets. Tickets will be will issued 48-hours prior to the event, via email/inside your Ticketleader.ca account.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE THERE TICKETING FEES AND TAX?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yes. We use a 3rd party ticketing site and they don’t work for free. The fees have been negotiated for the benefit of our guests and continue to be minimal. Regarding tax, only GST is charged on tickets. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW MUCH IS PARKING?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Parking lots are run by the PNE and thus still to be determined.  But, it is a beer festival so please do not drive to the event. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            IS THERE HANDICAP ACCESS AND PARKING?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yes. If you require parking for the disabled, there will be spots onsite. Proof of age is required to gain entry. So, you can bring your kids, as long as they are 19 years or older.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            CAN I BRING MY DOG? \n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Sorry, no pets allowed.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            Will security will be present at the event?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          As always, the PNE security team will be on hand making sure all runs safe and smoothly at VCBW.No backpacks will be allowed into the event. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE OUTSIDE FOOD AND DRINK ALLOWED AT THE EVENT?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Sorry but no outside food or drink is permitted to enter the premises. At the time of this being written, masks nor vaccine passports are not required and thus VCBW would not require them.Please read our Health and Safety Protocols for complete details.\n        \n         \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yes, in the designated smoking area only.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            MORE ABOUT THE MOSS\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          In a musical landscape with fewer boundaries than ever before, THE MOSS’s exuberant brand of alternative rock spans genres, eras, and even oceans.The Utah-via-Hawaii group was born on the shores of Oahu in 2015, as teenage buddies Tyke James (vocals/guitar) and Addison Sharp (guitar) picked up a gig serenading diners at local taco trucks in between surf sessions. Naturally, their songs took shape in the spirit of the island, imbued with the joyfulness and breeziness of reggae culture yet cut with the introspection and communal spirit of mainland indie acts like Pinegrove and Cage the Elephant.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n\n    \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            MORE ABOUT OLIVER HAZARD\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          While some musiciansare scheming to go viral, the Waterville, OH indie-folk band Oliver Hazard has been killing it the old-fashioned way: squeezing into a van, traversing a tangle of Interstates, and winning over fans one city at a time. They created a Living Room Tour, where one fan would host the band and invite over some friends. They played 60 shows across the U.S. in 2019 alone. Such is the ethic that’s made Oliver Hazard a case study in smarts, hustle, and unrelenting charm.Since then, Oliver Hazard — Mike Belazis (frontman), Devin East (guitarist) and Nate Miner (keyboardist) — have released a pair of albums (34 N. River, Oliver Hazard) and two EPs (The Flood, Northern Lights). The trio has gone on to headline tours, created their own festival Oliver Hazard Day, played Bonnaroo and Mountain Jam, and amassed nearly 850K Spotify monthly listeners. On December 6, the band will release its latest EP, Raindrop River (Nettwerk), a collection of warmly harmonic sing-alongs that celebrates an earnest, uncomplicated band at its peak.“Our music is a lot more heartfelt, because we’re actually playing together in a room. It’s pretty old school, but so are we,” Mike says. “Oliver Hazard wasn’t an overnight success. It’s not like we got two million followers on TikTok and all of a sudden the venues were full. We really had to be intentional about our shows. And we didn’t want to abandon that sense of place and community that helped us get to where we are.” instagram | spotify\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n PLACE?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          VCBW will be taking place the PNE Fairgrounds at 2901 E. Hastings in Vancouver, BC.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            REMIND ME THE BASIC DETAILS (DATE, TIME, ETC.)\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          SATURDAY JULY 12, 202512PM-4PM (Afternoon Tasting)5PM - 9PM (Evening Tasting)THE CONCERTSThe MossOliver HazardHarbourTHE PRODUCTSCraft BeerCidersBC Natural WinesWings + Other Foods\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW MUCH ARE TICKETS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Tickets start at their lowest price and as they sell and as the event gets closer, ticket prices increase.There are two categories of tickets: GA and GA+GA tickets start at $30 and will eventually end up at their regular price of $49, before selling out.GA+ tickets start at $55 and will eventually end up at their regular price of $74, before selling out. There are limited amount of GA+ tickets.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN GA AND GA+TICKETS AND WHAT IS INCLUDED IN EACH?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          GA TICKETAdmission During the Tasting its For (Aft vs. Eve)Souvenir Tasting CupThe ConcertsGA+ TICKETAll GA perks+*$30 Worth of Tokens*Private GA+ Entrance Private GA+ Bathrooms\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            IS THE EVENT RAIN OR SHINE?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yep!  We will be soaking up the rays of sun or frolicking within the drops of rain.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW DO TOKENS WORKS? HOW MUCH ARE SAMPLES?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Each product is purchased at the event using the festival token. Tokens can be pre-purchased or purchased onsite.Most, if not all beverage samples at VCBW are about $2 (+tax) worth of tokens .Food is available for purchase on site using credit/debit cards.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW DO I GET ACCESS TO THE PRE-SALE WINDOWS, DISCOUNTED TICKETS AND VIP EVENTS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Make sure you are on the Feaster list.  This is where any and all of the above will be released. Sign up for the list on the VCBW website.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            DO YOU SELL DESIGNATED DRIVER TICKETS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          We do not have a different ticket available for DDs. We welcome designated drivers and have thus the ticket is now a-la-carte in that you are just purchasing admission and if you want to sample alcohol, you’d purchase tokens to do so. Purchasing a GA ticket also gives the DD access to many food items, the concerts, non-alc beverage samples and entertainment. DO NOT DRINK AND DRIVE!\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHEN CAN I BUY TICKETS TO VCBW?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          All tickets for this event are purchased through ticketleader.ca. Pre-sale begins after March!\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            DO I NEED TO PRINT MY TICKET?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          No. All tickets are 100% mobile!\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE TICKETS REFUNDABLE?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          VCBW tickets are non-refundable. Tickets are transferable and thus can be given away to friends or sold on 3rd party sites. We do not hold any responsibility for tickets that are bought, sold, given away or received privately as there is no way to trace them to the new buyer. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHAT ABOUT IF IT IS POSTPONED?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          If the event is postponed for any reason, tickets will not be refunded.  All tickets will be valid for the next VCBW.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            IS THERE A TICKET LIMIT?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          No, there is not.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW ARE TICKETS DELIVERED?  \n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Tickets are all mobile tickets. Tickets will be will issued 48-hours prior to the event, via email/inside your Ticketleader.ca account.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE THERE TICKETING FEES AND TAX?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yes. We use a 3rd party ticketing site and they don’t work for free. The fees have been negotiated for the benefit of our guests and continue to be minimal. Regarding tax, only GST is charged on tickets. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW MUCH IS PARKING?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Parking lots are run by the PNE and thus still to be determined.  But, it is a beer festival so please do not drive to the event. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            IS THERE HANDICAP ACCESS AND PARKING?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yes. If you require parking for the disabled, there will be spots onsite. There are ramps where needed for wheelchair and more gradual ups and downs where necessary.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE THERE VOLUNTEER TICKETS AND HOW DO THEY WORK?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          If you would like to volunteer at this event, please contact us using the contact link.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHAT AGE DO I HAVE TO BE TO ATTEND? CAN I BRING MY KIDS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Every single person attending has to be 19 years or older, with no exceptions.  Proof of age is required to gain entry. So, you can bring your kids, as long as they are 19 years or older.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            CAN I BRING MY DOG? \n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Sorry, no pets allowed.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            Will security will be present at the event?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          As always, the PNE security team will be on hand making sure all runs safe and smoothly at VCBW.No backpacks will be allowed into the event. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE OUTSIDE FOOD AND DRINK ALLOWED AT THE EVENT?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Sorry but no outside food or drink is permitted to enter the premises. You may bring a refillable water bottle inside.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            DO I HAVE TO WEAR A MASK OR BE VACCINATED?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Safety is our primary priority and VCBW is committed to hosting a safe event. To help ensure we can move forward, VCBW will follow all local, provincial and federal mandatory requirements with respect to Covid restrictions. VCBW will not implement any additional restrictions. At the time of this being written, masks nor vaccine passports are not required and thus VCBW would not require them.Please read our Health and Safety Protocols for complete details.\n        \n         \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yes, in the designated smoking area only.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            MORE ABOUT THE MOSS\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          In a musical landscape with fewer boundaries than ever before, THE MOSS’s exuberant brand of alternative rock spans genres, eras, and even oceans.The Utah-via-Hawaii group was born on the shores of Oahu in 2015, as teenage buddies Tyke James (vocals/guitar) and Addison Sharp (guitar) picked up a gig serenading diners at local taco trucks in between surf sessions. Naturally, their songs took shape in the spirit of the island, imbued with the joyfulness and breeziness of reggae culture yet cut with the introspection and communal spirit of mainland indie acts like Pinegrove and Cage the Elephant.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n\n    \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            MORE ABOUT OLIVER HAZARD\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          While some musiciansare scheming to go viral, the Waterville, OH indie-folk band Oliver Hazard has been killing it the old-fashioned way: squeezing into a van, traversing a tangle of Interstates, and winning over fans one city at a time. They created a Living Room Tour, where one fan would host the band and invite over some friends. They played 60 shows across the U.S. in 2019 alone. Such is the ethic that’s made Oliver Hazard a case study in smarts, hustle, and unrelenting charm.Since then, Oliver Hazard — Mike Belazis (frontman), Devin East (guitarist) and Nate Miner (keyboardist) — have released a pair of albums (34 N. River, Oliver Hazard) and two EPs (The Flood, Northern Lights). The trio has gone on to headline tours, created their own festival Oliver Hazard Day, played Bonnaroo and Mountain Jam, and amassed nearly 850K Spotify monthly listeners. On December 6, the band will release its latest EP, Raindrop River (Nettwerk), a collection of warmly harmonic sing-alongs that celebrates an earnest, uncomplicated band at its peak.“Our music is a lot more heartfelt, because we’re actually playing together in a room. It’s pretty old school, but so are we,” Mike says. “Oliver Hazard wasn’t an overnight success. It’s not like we got two million followers on TikTok and all of a sudden the venues were full. We really had to be intentional about our shows. And we didn’t want to abandon that sense of place and community that helped us get to where we are.” instagram | spotify\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n \n\n\n\n\n\n\n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n          \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            MORE ABOUT Harbour\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Since their formation in 2014, HARBOUR has gone from packing rooms in their native Cincinnati, to selling out venues across the United States. Members Ryan Green (vocals/guitar), Jarett Lewis (guitar), Ryan Sulken (drums), Walker Atkinson (bass), and Devon Turner (guitar) have curated an indie pop/rock sound that has garnered millions of listeners worldwide across all music platforms.Their latest album - “To Chase My Dreams, Or To Just Lie Down?” was released in February, 2023. PLACE?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          VCBW will be taking place the PNE Fairgrounds at 2901 E. Hastings in Vancouver, BC.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            REMIND ME THE BASIC DETAILS (DATE, TIME, ETC.)\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          SATURDAY JULY 12, 202512PM-4PM (Afternoon Tasting)5PM - 9PM (Evening Tasting)THE CONCERTSThe MossOliver HazardHarbourTHE PRODUCTSCraft BeerCidersBC Natural WinesWings + Other Foods\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW MUCH ARE TICKETS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Tickets start at their lowest price and as they sell and as the event gets closer, ticket prices increase.There are two categories of tickets: GA and GA+GA tickets start at $30 and will eventually end up at their regular price of $49, before selling out.GA+ tickets start at $55 and will eventually end up at their regular price of $74, before selling out. There are limited amount of GA+ tickets.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHAT IS THE DIFFERENCE BETWEEN GA AND GA+TICKETS AND WHAT IS INCLUDED IN EACH?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          GA TICKETAdmission During the Tasting its For (Aft vs. Eve)Souvenir Tasting CupThe ConcertsGA+ TICKETAll GA perks+*$30 Worth of Tokens*Private GA+ Entrance Private GA+ Bathrooms\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            IS THE EVENT RAIN OR SHINE?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yep!  We will be soaking up the rays of sun or frolicking within the drops of rain.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW DO TOKENS WORKS? HOW MUCH ARE SAMPLES?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Each product is purchased at the event using the festival token. Tokens can be pre-purchased or purchased onsite.Most, if not all beverage samples at VCBW are about $2 (+tax) worth of tokens .Food is available for purchase on site using credit/debit cards.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW DO I GET ACCESS TO THE PRE-SALE WINDOWS, DISCOUNTED TICKETS AND VIP EVENTS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Make sure you are on the Feaster list.  This is where any and all of the above will be released. Sign up for the list on the VCBW website.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            DO YOU SELL DESIGNATED DRIVER TICKETS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          We do not have a different ticket available for DDs. We welcome designated drivers and have thus the ticket is now a-la-carte in that you are just purchasing admission and if you want to sample alcohol, you’d purchase tokens to do so. Purchasing a GA ticket also gives the DD access to many food items, the concerts, non-alc beverage samples and entertainment. DO NOT DRINK AND DRIVE!\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHEN CAN I BUY TICKETS TO VCBW?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          All tickets for this event are purchased through ticketleader.ca. Pre-sale begins after March!\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            DO I NEED TO PRINT MY TICKET?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          No. All tickets are 100% mobile!\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE TICKETS REFUNDABLE?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          VCBW tickets are non-refundable. Tickets are transferable and thus can be given away to friends or sold on 3rd party sites. We do not hold any responsibility for tickets that are bought, sold, given away or received privately as there is no way to trace them to the new buyer. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHAT ABOUT IF IT IS POSTPONED?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          If the event is postponed for any reason, tickets will not be refunded.  All tickets will be valid for the next VCBW.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            IS THERE A TICKET LIMIT?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          No, there is not.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW ARE TICKETS DELIVERED?  \n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Tickets are all mobile tickets. Tickets will be will issued 48-hours prior to the event, via email/inside your Ticketleader.ca account.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE THERE TICKETING FEES AND TAX?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yes. We use a 3rd party ticketing site and they don’t work for free. The fees have been negotiated for the benefit of our guests and continue to be minimal. Regarding tax, only GST is charged on tickets. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            HOW MUCH IS PARKING?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Parking lots are run by the PNE and thus still to be determined.  But, it is a beer festival so please do not drive to the event. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            IS THERE HANDICAP ACCESS AND PARKING?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yes. If you require parking for the disabled, there will be spots onsite. There are ramps where needed for wheelchair and more gradual ups and downs where necessary.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE THERE VOLUNTEER TICKETS AND HOW DO THEY WORK?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          If you would like to volunteer at this event, please contact us using the contact link.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            WHAT AGE DO I HAVE TO BE TO ATTEND? CAN I BRING MY KIDS?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Every single person attending has to be 19 years or older, with no exceptions.  Proof of age is required to gain entry. So, you can bring your kids, as long as they are 19 years or older.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            CAN I BRING MY DOG? \n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Sorry, no pets allowed.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            Will security will be present at the event?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          As always, the PNE security team will be on hand making sure all runs safe and smoothly at VCBW.No backpacks will be allowed into the event. \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            ARE OUTSIDE FOOD AND DRINK ALLOWED AT THE EVENT?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Sorry but no outside food or drink is permitted to enter the premises. You may bring a refillable water bottle inside.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n    \n  \n    \n\n      \n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n          \n            DO I HAVE TO WEAR A MASK OR BE VACCINATED?\n          \n          \n            \n              \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Safety is our primary priority and VCBW is committed to hosting a safe event. To help ensure we can move forward, VCBW will follow all local, provincial and federal mandatory requirements with respect to Covid restrictions. VCBW will not implement any additional restrictions. At the time of this being written, masks nor vaccine passports are not required and thus VCBW would not require them.Please read our Health and Safety Protocols for complete details.\n        \n         \n                \n              \n            \n          \n        \n      \n      \n        \n          Yes, in the designated smoking area only.\n        \n      \n\n      \n        \n This exhibition delves into the life stories of local animals and plants—how they relate to each other and how they connect people to nature in the city. Scenic design, videos, taxidermy, crowdsourcing technologies, and the display of natural specimens breathe life into these tales of co-habitation. The immersive nature of the exhibition, including hands-on activities, encourages visitors to examine their relationship with nature, think about momentarily disconnecting from their devices, and find equilibrium with the natural world around them.  **CONTEST CLOSED** Thank you so much to everyone who submitted their nature photos! The contest winner has been notified.Hancock Wildlife Foundation (HWF) presents a streaming live view of this bald eagle nest located in Delta, British Columbia, Canada.There have been eagles in this territory in Delta, British Columbia, not far from the Tsawwassen Ferry, since at least the late 1990s. They initially took over and rebuilt a red tail hawk nest, then nested on high tension power poles for a few years, then moved back to the nest in 2010 and successfully raised two eaglets.  A camera was installed for 2011, and as of fall 2018, Hancock Wildlife Foundation have watched the pair successfully raise eleven young eagles.
